    "The non-causal version employs bidirectional LSTM in each layer, whereas the causal version uses unidirectional LSTM.",
    "to the pattern-matching approaches 18 that produce subject-specific utterances but with limited generalizability.",
    "Many earlier studies employed high-density electrode coverage over the cortex, providing many distinct neural signals 5, 10, 17, 30, 37.",
    "One question we directly addressed was whether higher-density coverage improves decoding.",
    "Surprisingly, we found a high decoding performance in terms of spectrogram PCC with both low-density and higher (hybrid) density grid coverages (Fig. 3c)."
